# Pomodoro Timer Implementation Complete

I've successfully updated the Pomodoro timer to include the features you requested! 

## Changes Made
- **Custom Time Input**: Added a sleek, transparent number input field directly underneath the "Focus" title, integrated nicely with the glassmorphism design. You can now define your own session length in minutes instead of being restricted to the default 25 minutes.
- **Sound Effect**: Implemented a modern, sweet-sounding notification chime using the Web Audio API. It plays automatically when the countdown reaches 00:00.
- **Refined Styling**: Updated the CSS styling to ensure the new input field feels cohesive with the dark mode and gradient aesthetics of the page.
- **Robust Logic**: Modified the JavaScript to correctly read your custom time preference when you start or reset the timer, seamlessly adjusting the progress ring visualization accordingly.

## Validation Results
I tested these modifications using a browser subagent and verified that:
1. Setting the timer to a custom duration (e.g., 1 minute) works perfectly.
2. The countdown accurately tracks the new time.
3. Upon reaching 00:00, the user interface remains responsive and allows you to "Start" a new session without needing a page refresh.
4. The custom chime sound fires reliably at the end of the session.

